<span id="freeTextContainer11867277042349094600"><b>In this groundbreaking book, Matthieu Ricard makes a passionate case for happiness as a goal that deserves as least as much energy as any other in our lives.</b><br/><br/> Wealth? Fitness? Career success? How can we possibly place these above true and lasting well-being? Drawing from works of fiction and poetry, Western philosophy, Buddhist beliefs, scientific research, and personal exp</span>
  <span id="freeText11867277042349094600" style="display:none"><b>In this groundbreaking book, Matthieu Ricard makes a passionate case for happiness as a goal that deserves as least as much energy as any other in our lives.</b><br /><br /> Wealth? Fitness? Career success? How can we possibly place these above true and lasting well-being? Drawing from works of fiction and poetry, Western philosophy, Buddhist beliefs, scientific research, and personal experience, Ricard weaves an inspirational and forward-looking account of how we can begin to rethink our realities in a fast-moving modern world. With its revelatory lessons and exercises, <i>Happiness</i> is an eloquent and stimulating guide to a happier life.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11867277042349094600" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

