      <div id="aboutAuthor" class=" clearFloats bigBox"><div class="h2Container gradientHeaderContainer"><h2 class="brownBackground"><a href="/author/show/55728.Matthieu_Ricard">About Matthieu Ricard</a></h2></div><div class="bigBoxBody"><div class="bigBoxContent containerWithHeaderContent">
          <div class='bookAuthorProfile'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__topContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__photoContainer'>
<a href="/author/show/55728.Matthieu_Ricard"><div class='bookAuthorProfile__photo' style='background-image: url(https://images.gr-assets.com/authors/1312498034p3/55728.jpg);'></div>
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__widgetContainer'>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__name'>
<a href="/author/show/55728.Matthieu_Ricard">Matthieu Ricard
</a></div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__followerCount'>
608
followers
</div>

</div>
</div>
<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer9815278929687471777">Matthieu Ricard, a Buddhist monk, trained as a molecular biologist before moving to Nepal to study Buddhism. He is the author of <em>The Monk and the Philosopher</em> (with his father, Jean-François Revel); <em>The Quantum and the Lotus</em> (with Trinh Thuan); <em>Happiness</em>; <em>The Art of Meditation</em>; <em>Altruism: The Power of Compassion</em>; <em>A Plea for the Animals</em>; and <em>Beyond the Self: Conversations between Buddhism and Neurosc</em></span>
  <span id="freeText9815278929687471777" style="display:none">Matthieu Ricard, a Buddhist monk, trained as a molecular biologist before moving to Nepal to study Buddhism. He is the author of <em>The Monk and the Philosopher</em> (with his father, Jean-François Revel); <em>The Quantum and the Lotus</em> (with Trinh Thuan); <em>Happiness</em>; <em>The Art of Meditation</em>; <em>Altruism: The Power of Compassion</em>; <em>A Plea for the Animals</em>; and <em>Beyond the Self: Conversations between Buddhism and Neuroscience</em> (with Wolf Singer). He has published several books of photography, including <em>Motionless Journey</em> and <em>Tibet: An Inner Journey</em>, and is the French interpreter for the Dalai Lama.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9815278929687471777" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
</div>

<div class="clear"></div></div></div><div class="bigBoxBottom"></div></div>

  

